<br />
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">The strategy for this deck is relatively simple. Using the special text of Legolas, G and Aragorn&#39;s bow combined with ranger abilities, the goal is to wound the opponent&#39;s shadow side as much as possible before the skirmish phase. Then we can use Arwen as a powerhouse against Nazgul, Merry makes an overall strong fighter, and then use Aragorn to fight, and then heal a companion every fellowship phase.<br />
<br />
The shadow is just a basic Nazgul shadow side.<br />
<br />
As far as the sites, pull aragorn with Prancing Pony, and a majority of the sites are either rivers or forest to help out with your ranger cards. Also you may want to save minions for Ford of Bruinen, and try to stop the fellowship with your nazgul<br />
<br />
Thanks, and please review!! </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
